external_knowledge:
Total bytes of network traffic refers to the sum of bytes uploaded and downloaded; 
Clients are ranked based on their total bytes in descending order within each country;
The top 3 clients per country are selected;
Access logs include access date, access type, and user name.

sql:
SELECT traffic_id, SUM(bytes) AS total_bytes, COUNT(DISTINCT clients) AS unique_clients
FROM network_traffic
GROUP BY traffic_id;

SELECT type_id, SUM(bytes) AS total_bytes
FROM traffic_type_data
GROUP BY type_id;

