External knowledge required to fully understand the question includes:
- 'traffic types' refers to the different categories of network traffic (e.g., web, file transfer);
- 'cumulative network traffic in bytes' indicates the total amount of network traffic in bytes accumulated over time for each region and traffic type;
- 'unique users' are users with distinct IDs who have accessed the network traffic data;
- 'maximum levels of access hierarchy' refers to the deepest level of access recursion (up to 3 levels) in the user access patterns.
